    <p class="intro">Coding. It basically runs the world as we know it, but the vast majority of people aren’t even aware of its existence, let along what it even is. Unless you happen to be one of the few people who can call themselves a ‘programmer’ or a ‘coder’, then you should keep reading.
        Through this website we will explore the question ‘What is coding?’, and we will go into more detail about some basic coding background and coding 101. We will look briefly at the question of ‘programming vs coding’ and what the difference really is, and we will explore a few of the more common languages and how you can start learning them.</p>
    <div class="presentation">
        <h1>What is the definition of coding ?</h1>
        <p>Before we start, I want you to answer this question for yourself. Right-click somewhere inside your browser window, and select ‘View Page Source’. Scroll through the window that pops up and sees if you recognize or understand anything.</p>
        <p>As you may have expected, you were just viewing the code behind this webpage. Most of it is written in HTML, but there are little bits of CSS and JavaScript here and there (but more on that later).</p>
        <p><img src="../public/assets/img/yes.gif" class="img-article"></p>
        <p>Now, in simple terms, let’s define coding as the basic act of writing  – in a programming language – a script that a computer can understand. This script will tell the computer to behave in a certain way, to do a certain thing, and to, ultimately, perform the actions that you want it to – if your code is right.</p>
    </div>
