        <p>What is coding? While we have defined coding as the act of writing a script in a language that your computer can understand, let’s get down and dirty and have a look at some coding background.</p>
        <p>In reality, your computer doesn’t understand the code you have written very well at all. In fact, all that it understands is ‘Yes’ and ‘No’ (or 1 and 0 if you are familiar with Binary code). While the code that you write isn’t really understood at all, the results of it are, as it tells your computer what to do.</p>
